____________________________________-------

Subscription
└── Azure Resource Manager (control plane)
    └── Resource Group
        ├── Virtual Network (VNet)
        │   ├── Public Subnet
        │   │   ├── NSG (Inbound Internet allowed)
        │   │   ├── UDR (0.0.0.0/0 → Internet)
        │   │   ├── Azure Bastion / App Gateway
        │   │   └── Public IP
        │   │
        │   └── Private Subnet
        │       ├── NSG (No Internet inbound)                 #NSG → allow / deny traffic-----N/w security groups

                                                              #UDR → where traffic goes-----User defined routes
        │       ├── UDR (0.0.0.0/0 → NAT / Firewall)
        │       ├── NIC
        │       │   └── Virtual Machine
        │       │
        │       └── Private Endpoint
        │           └── Storage Account
        │
        ├── Network Security Groups (logical)
        ├── Route Tables (UDR)
        ├── Storage Account
        │   └── Blob Container (Terraform State)
        │
        └── Monitoring & Security
            ├── Azure Monitor
            ├── Log Analytics
            └── Defender for Cloud
            ___________________________________________-
            1️⃣ Security (biggest reason)

Private subnet has no direct Internet route

NIC gets only a private IP

VM cannot be reached directly from Internet
__________________________
What actually decides Public vs Private subnet?

A subnet is considered PUBLIC or PRIVATE based on three things:

1️⃣ Route to Internet (UDR / system routes)
2️⃣ Presence of Public IPs on NICs
3️⃣ NSG rules
